<HEADLINE>
<P>
PRO FOOTBALL DAILY REPORT; RAIDERS; INJURY LIST SHORT AFTER VICTORY IN SPAIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LONNIE WHITE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Rookie linebacker James Folston's twisted ankle was the only injury suffered 
by the Raiders in the 25-22 overtime exhibition victory over the Denver Broncos 
in American Bowl '94 on Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 The team will return to its normal twice-a-day schedule today. The Raiders 
leave Saturday afternoon for Dallas to play the Cowboys in a Sunday night 
exhibition. LONNIE WHITE 
</P>
