<HEADLINE>
<P>
WOMEN'S TENNIS; GRAF BREEZES IN OPENER AT CARLSBAD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Top-ranked Steffi Graf used her overpowering game to dominate France's Alexia 
Dechaume-Balleret, 6-0, 6-1, Tuesday night in a second-round match in the 
$400,000 Toshiba Tennis Classic. 
</P>
<P>
 Graf, who had a first-round bye, needed just 47 minutes to move into today's 
third round against two-time NCAA champion Lisa Raymond. 
</P>
<P>
 "From anywhere, I felt like I could hit winners," Graf said. "It was just a 
really good feeling out there, especially with my forehand. It just went where 
I wanted it to." 
</P>
<P>
 Graf, who entered with a two-match losing streak, made quick work of 
Dechaume-Balleret as she won the first 11 games. 
</P>
<P>
 Lindsay Davenport, her serve humming on the hard courts, also enjoyed a quick 
afternoon of work, breezing past Stephanie Rottier, 6-2, 6-3. 
</P>
<P>
 Davenport, ranked sixth in the world and seeded fourth, surrendered only 12 
points on her serve. 
</P>
