<HEADLINE>
<P>
FISHING REPORT: CONVICT LAKE CAN'T HOLD TROPHY TROUT BREAKOUT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The hanging of big fish is becoming a popular pastime at Convict Lake. 
</P>
<P>
 "Every day they're bringing in no less than four and as many as six fish in 
the three-, four- and five-pound range," said David DeSurra, owner of the 
concession at the picturesque Eastern Sierra reservoir. 
</P>
<P>
 And then there was the 6-pound 8-ounce rainbow -- the biggest catch in the 
region to date -- pulled from the inlet by Bill Evans of Upland.  
</P>
<P>
 "I have 32 pictures of big fish taken in the last week," DeSurra said, adding 
that there have also been plenty of limits of pan-size fish coming in. 
</P>
</TEXT>
