<P>
OWNERS MISS UNION PAYMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ROSS NEWHAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Don Fehr, the baseball players' union executive director, said Tuesday his 
organization had not received a $7 million to $8 million pension payment from 
the owners due Aug. 1 from All-Star game receipts. 
</P>
<P>
 Richard Ravitch, the owners' chief negotiator, said the decision to withhold 
the payment was understandable since technically there is no bargaining 
agreement in place, but Eugene Orza, the union's associate general counsel, 
called it "an all-time low" and couldn't predict how the players would react. 
ROSS NEWHAN 
</P>
