<HEADLINE>
<P>
CITY TEAMS BEGIN TO HUDDLE UP; HIGH SCHOOL FOOTBALL: WITH TWO-A-DAYS BANNED, 
PRESEASON CONDITIONING IS OFF TO AN EARLY START. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE ELLING, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Sure, it's early. Sure, it's hot. 
</P>
<P>
 But this is precisely the way most City Section football coaches wanted it. 
</P>
<P>
 Preseason conditioning for City football teams already is underway, believed 
to be the earliest that players and coaches have been permitted to meet in 
preparation for the fall high school season. The season begins Sept. 9. 
</P>
<P>
 Because of rule changes backed by the City's L.A. Football Coaches Assn., 
two-a-day practices have been eliminated, but coaches were permitted to meet 
with players for conditioning drills starting Monday. The City is providing 
busing for players who live outside the San Fernando Valley. 
</P>
<P>
 Two-a-day practices were scrubbed because of their inherent advantage to 
schools on the traditional academic calendar. Players at year-round schools are 
in classes all morning. 
</P>
<P>
 "We have 13 schools on (the year-round calendar) and it wasn't really fair," 
City Commissioner Barbara Fiege said. "They can only practice once a day." 
</P>
<P>
 The conditioning period, during which teams also are permitted to walk through 
plays, ends Aug. 16. 
</P>
<P>
 From Aug. 17-19, players may practice while wearing helmets and shorts. On 
Aug. 22, practice in full pads begins. 
</P>
<P>
 Last summer, conditioning didn't begin until mid-August. 
</P>
<P>
 Predictably, there are trade-offs under the new schedule. 
</P>
<P>
 Reseda High players began conditioning Monday, while other schools are 
expected to begin at various times this week. It makes for a long season, to be 
sure. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's getting out of hand," said Reseda Coach Joel Schaeffer, who is entering 
his 16th season. "It takes away too much of the summer." 
</P>
<P>
 Conversely, Schaeffer said, the changes allow players to become gradually 
immersed in the sport, rather than be subjected to the two-a-day crash course. 
</P>
<P>
 Conditioning at Southern Section schools takes place August 22-24. Full 
practice begins August 25 with most openers set for Sept. 9. 
</P>
<P>
 At the behest of the football coaches association, the City also modified the 
playoff system. Instead of teams playing the season as members of the 3-A or 
4-A divisions, teams will be placed into the 3-A or 4-A playoffs based on 
won-loss records and perceived strength at the end of the season. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA080394-0064 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 066483 </DOCID>
