<BYLINE>
<P>
By DWAYNE BRAY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An Oxnard woman pleaded not guilty on Tuesday to charges of child endangerment 
and battery, two days after witnesses reported she dropped her 3-month-old baby 
over a 6-foot-high chain-link fence. 
</P>
<P>
 Witnesses told police that Aretha Chester dangled the infant over the fence 
Sunday in Sierra Linda Park while chasing after the child's father, her 
boyfriend, who had jumped over the gate. 
</P>
<P>
 Municipal Judge Herbert Curtis III ordered the 23-year-old defendant held at 
the Ventura County Jail in lieu of $25,000 bail. 
</P>
<P>
 As she waited in court to be led back to jail, Chester buried her face in her 
hands and sobbed. A preliminary hearing was set for Aug. 15. 
</P>
<P>
 Court officials said Chester has numerous past arrests and one conviction for 
battery, for which she is currently on probation. 
</P>
