<BYLINE>
<P>
By MATTHEW MOSK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The operator of an Ojai geophysical consulting firm was charged Tuesday with 
failure to file his tax returns, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 Richard W. Van Derck, 48, was charged with willfully failing to file tax 
returns for 1985, 1986 and 1988, according to a statement issued Tuesday by the 
U.S. attorney's office in Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
 Van Derck operated a consulting firm named Terranova and was aware of his 
responsibilities to file tax returns for his income from that business, 
according to the statement. 
</P>
