<P>
TV RATINGS; VIEWERS CAST A VOTE FOR THE LAUGHS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LEE MARGULIES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 CBS' "60 Minutes" and ABC's "20/20" cracked the Top 10, but otherwise it was 
comedy that dominated America's television viewing last week, according to 
ratings released Tuesday by the A. C. Nielsen Co. ABC's "Home Improvement" 
(starring Tim Allen) and "Grace Under Fire" were on top, followed by NBC's 
"Seinfeld" and "Frasier." 
</P>
<P>
 Yet CBS edged out its rivals in the network race, thanks to strong showings on 
Saturday, Sunday and Monday, where "The Nanny," running outside its usual time 
slot, tied at No. 17--its first finish in the Top 20. In its regular airing on 
Wednesday, it ranked 33rd. 
</P>
<P>
 Fox's effort to transfer the daytime children's hit "The Mighty Morphin Power 
Rangers" to prime time met with an unenthusiastic response from most viewers. 
The Friday night telecast ranked 80th among the week's 86 prime-time network 
programs--although Fox said it attracted 36% of the available children. 
