<P>
 PG&E Will Freeze Rates for Third Year: The San Francisco-based investor-owned 
utility will continue its rate freeze through 1995 instead of making increases 
of $285 million that would have taken effect Jan. 1.The company will also 
continue a $70-million rate reduction aimed at large industrial users. 
