<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: REAL ESTATE; HOUSING PERMITS ISSUED IN FIRST HALF OF 1994 REACH 
5-YEAR HIGH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Debora Vrana, Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Nearly 8,000 housing permits were issued in Orange County during the first 
half of the year, the biggest total for that period in five years, according to 
the Construction Industry Research Board. 
</P>
<P>
 Builders took out 7,966 housing permits, compared to 3,276 permits for the 
first half of 1993, the Burbank-based real estate group reported. The last time 
the total for the six-month period was higher was in 1989, when 8,890 permits 
were issued. 
</P>
