<TEXT>
<P>
 Rockwell: The Seal Beach company said Tuesday that it has completed the sale 
of its automotive plastics business to Cambridge Industries Inc. of Dearborn, 
Mich.Terms of the transaction were not disclosed. 
</P>
<P>
 The sale of Rockwell's plastics business, announced in May, includes three 
manufacturing plants in Centralia, Ill., and Lenoir and Newton, N.C. The 
plastics business has about 1,700 employees, 20 of whom are sales and 
engineering personnel working in the Troy, Mich., headquarters of Rockwell 
Automotive. 
</P>
<P>
 Cambridge said it will have annual revenue of about $300 million with the 
addition of Rockwell's automotive plastics business. 
