<P>
BRIEFCASE: REAL ESTATE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Debora Vrana, Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Course Work: The second golf course at Coto de Caza, the 4,000-acre planned 
community in south Orange County, is under construction and expected to open 
next spring.When the so-called South Course is completed, Coto will be the 
first private country club community in Orange County to offer 36 holes of 
championship golf.  
</P>
<P>
 "Anyone who has played our North Course knows how challenging and beautiful it 
is," said Tom Martin, vice president of sales and marketing for the company. 
"The intent of the design of our second course was to create a completely 
different golf experience." 
</P>
<P>
 Joining the club costs $20,000, with $5,000 down and three additional $5,000 
payments due each anniversary for three years. 
