<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY NEWSMAKERS: SATELLITE TECHNOLOGY MANAGEMENT NAMES CHIEF OPERATING 
OFFICER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * Michael Lindsay has been appointed to the newly created position of chief 
operating officer for Satellite Technology Management Inc., a Costa Mesa 
manufacturer of satellite and radio communications products. He was formerly 
chief operating officer of NuMedia Corp., a multimedia software developer. 
Before joining NuMedia, Lindsey was president of Dowty Communications, a data 
communications equipment manufacturer. 
</P>
<P>
 * Daniel Zukowski has joined the Santa Ana advertising and public relations 
agency of Roberts, Mealer & Co. as director of consumer public relations and 
public relations account manager. He was previously an account supervisor at 
Freeman/McCue. 
</P>
<P>
 * Mario Scubla has been appointed to head corporate information systems for 
Furon Co., a Laguna Niguel polymer manufacturer. Scubla joined Furon from 
Magnetek Inc. in Los Angeles, where he served as corporate M.I.S. director, 
with additional responsibilities that included procurement and serving as 
managing director of an Italian affiliate. Before that he was with Smith 
International and Martin Marietta. 
</P>
<P>
 * Bruce Channing and John Draper have joined the board of directors of 
Saddleback Memorial Foundation, the fund-raising arm of Saddleback Memorial 
Medical Center. Channing is the city manager of Laguna Hills, and Draper is a 
certified financial planner with the investment company Smith Barney. 
</P>
<P>
 * Peter D. Behrendt has been elected to the board of directors of Western 
Digital Corp., an Irvine computer products company. Behrendt is chairman, 
president and chief executive of Exabyte Corp., a tape storage products 
manufacturer in Boulder, Colo. He succeeds Jack Peltason, president of the 
University of California system, who resigned at the end of June, citing the 
press of duties at the university system.  
</P>
<P>
 * Henri A. Cuddihy has been appointed medical director of Compremier, 
PacifiCare Health Systems' HMO for workers' compensation services in Cypress. 
His experience in occupational medicine includes serving on the advisory 
committee for the state Official Medical Fee Schedule and the Health Care 
Organization Data Advisory Board, and medical director of the Foothill 
Industrial Medical Clinics in Irwindale and El Monte.  
</P>
<P>
 * Joshua D.J. Sharfman has joined Digitalk Inc., a Santa Ana provider of 
computer programming tools, as vice president of development. He previously 
spent nine years at Dassault Systemes, most recently as executive vice 
president of research and development. 
</P>
<P>
 * Geoffrey M. Knoerzer has been appointed to the newly created position of 
vice president of operations at Subscriber Computing Inc., a Laguna Hills 
company that provides software and consulting services for personal 
communications carriers. He was formerly development director for Cincinnati 
Bell Information Systems' Chicago operations, and before that, director and 
general manager of Comptech, its paging software division in Seattle. 
</P>
<P>
 * Lisa Rehnborg has been appointed director of corporate culture and human 
resources for Nutrilite Products Inc. in Buena Park, a subsidiary of Amway 
Corp. She has been with the company for eight years, most recently as manager 
of marketing and sales services. 
</P>
<P>
 * Manuel J. Torrez has joined Orange National Bank as vice president and 
manager of its east Orange office. Previously, he was vice president and 
manager of Eldorado Bank's Orange office. Before joining Eldorado, Torrez was 
vice president and manager of Bank of America's Anaheim commercial business 
banking department. 
</P>
