VALLEYWIDE FOCUS: DANCE SHOWS TO HELP FEED AIDS PATIENTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ANTONIO OLIVO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 AIDS-afflicted men, women and children restricted to their Valley homes will 
receive a boost this weekend with the return of choreographer Doug Caldwell's 
benefit dance concert "Love Is All That Matters." 
</P>
<P>
 The show will generate funds for Project Angel Food, a meal-on-wheels program 
for those who are homebound due to AIDS-related illnesses. 
</P>
<P>
 "Love Is All That Matters" played to sold-out crowds in April and May.  
</P>
<P>
 It returns with shows at the Performing Arts Center at 15934 Strathern St., 
Van Nuys, on Friday and Saturday at 8 p.m. and on Sunday at 2 and 8 p.m. 
Tickets are $12.  
</P>
