<HEADLINE>
<P>
SANTA CLARITA / ANTELOPE VALLEY; EXOTIC DANCE CLUB DELAYS REOPENING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A controversial exotic dance club just outside Santa Clarita has postponed its 
reopening for at least two weeks for unspecified reasons, and now tentatively 
plans to open its doors Aug. 15. 
</P>
<P>
 Castaic Junction: A Gentleman's Club, located just north of Six Flags Magic 
Mountain, was closed by police July 21 because the club did not have the proper 
county permits.Club officials said they hoped to reopen Monday, but failed to 
do so. 
</P>
<P>
 An answering machine at Castaic Junction's listed phone number states the club 
will tentatively stage its "grand opening" Aug. 15 as a restaurant with a full 
bar and live exotic dancing. 
</P>
<P>
 Castaic Junction has stirred controversy since opening in late June. The 
building's owner obtained a court order forcing all-nude female dancers to wear 
bikinis, claiming the dancers violated the club's lease. 
</P>
<P>
 Numerous protests have also come from local residents, but club officials said 
their crowds were good until the shutdown. 
</P>
</TEXT>
