<HEADLINE>
<P>
FOR THE RECORD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Haiti address -- White House Chief of Staff Leon E. Panetta did not explicitly 
state that President Clinton is planning to address the nation on the subject 
of Haiti, as The Times reported Tuesday as a result of an editing error. 
Panetta indicated, and other Administration sources confirm, that such an 
address might be given if the President decides to use force to oust the 
military regime. 
</P>
</TEXT>
